cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.SI, cs.DS

The paper discusses the detection of botnets, which is a topic related to computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The interception technique used in the paper involves monitoring system calls made by communication applications, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The idea of log correlation also involves analyzing data from multiple hosts, which is related to distributed systems (cs.DS) and possibly social networks (cs.SI) if the hosts are connected through social relationships.
